Section 1:
1 L.D. 987
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 ENVIRONMENT AND NATURAL RESOURCES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 419, L.D. 987, “An Act Clarifying
10 Exemptions from the Notification Requirements for Products Containing PFAS”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act Clarifying Exemptions from the Law Regulating Products Containing PFAS'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §1614, sub-§4, ¶I, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 630, §1, is amended
16 to read:
17 I. A motor vehicle or motor vehicle equipment regulated under a federal motor vehicle
18 safety standard, as defined in 49 United States Code, Section 30102(a)(10), and any
19 other motor vehicle, including an off-highway vehicle or specialty motor vehicle, such
20 as an all-terrain vehicle, a side-by-side vehicle, construction, forestry or farm
21 equipment or a personal assistive mobility device, except that the exemption under this
22 paragraph does not apply to any textile article or refrigerant that is included in or as a
23 component part of such products;'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, changes the title and
2288 replaces the bill. It amends the law regulating products containing PFAS to clarify the
2299 scope of the exemption under that law for motor vehicles and motor vehicle equipment as
3300 that exemption relates to construction and forestry equipment.
3311 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3322 (See attached)
